us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame

Class FrameLineSegment2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.FrameLineSegment2D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LineSegment2DBasics, LineSegment2DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.EpsilonComparable<FrameLineSegment2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometricallyComparable<FrameLineSegment2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometryObject<FrameLineSegment2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Settable<FrameLineSegment2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, FixedFrameLineSegment2DBasics, FrameChangeable, FrameLineSegment2DBasics, FrameLineSegment2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder

    public class FrameLineSegment2D
extends java.lang.Object
implements FrameLineSegment2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometryObject<FrameLineSegment2D>
    FrameLineSegment2D is a 2D line segment expressed in a given reference frame.

    In addition to representing a LineSegment2DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameLineSegment2D. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on line segments occur in the same coordinate system. Also, via the method changeFrame(ReferenceFrame), one can easily calculates the value of a point in different reference frames.

    Because a FrameLineSegment2D extends LineSegment2DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring LineSegment2DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameLineSegment2D.

      • changeFrame

        public void changeFrame(ReferenceFrame desiredFrame)
        Transforms this geometry such that the transformation represents the same geometry but from the perspective of another reference frame: desiredFrame.

        Once the geometry is transformed, the reference frame is updated to desiredFrame. In the case, this.referenceFrame == desiredFrame, this method does nothing.

        Specified by:
        changeFrame in interface FrameChangeable
        Parameters:
        desiredFrame - the reference frame in which this geometry is to be expressed.

      • changeFrameAndProjectToXYPlane

        public void changeFrameAndProjectToXYPlane(ReferenceFrame desiredFrame)
        Performs a transformation of the line segment such that it is expressed in a new frame desireFrame.

        Because the transformation between two reference frames is a 3D transformation, the result of transforming this line segment 2D can result in a line segment 3D. This method projects the result of the transformation onto the XY-plane.

        Specified by:
        changeFrameAndProjectToXYPlane in interface FrameLineSegment2DBasics
        Parameters:
        desiredFrame - the reference frame in which the line segment is to be expressed.
